## Soft Deletes
{{- if .HasProfile}}
{{- if .Profile.DB.SoftDeletes}}
**Soft deletes are required.** Use `deleted_at TIMESTAMPTZ NULL`.

- Never issue `DELETE` in application code
- All queries must filter `WHERE deleted_at IS NULL` unless explicitly fetching deleted records
- Unique constraints must account for soft deletes (partial indexes: `WHERE deleted_at IS NULL`)
{{- else}}
**Hard deletes are used.** Document any exceptions explicitly in the migration.
{{- end}}
{{- else}}
<!-- Soft delete strategy: deleted_at column or hard deletes? -->
{{- end}}

